<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, March by Krishnas Hand-drawn chariots, cymbals and conga drums marked a 
march by 2,000 Hare Krishnas along Ocean Front Walk from Santa Monica to Venice 
beach Sunday. The event had two motives -- one to protest a $9.7-million court 
judgment which members say threatens the movement, the other to welcome 100 
Hare Krishnas on a walk from San Francisco to Tijuana. Police said the march 
attracted 20,000, drawn by the spectacle of the chariots and costumed marchers 
and by free food. Music and entertainment, staged at the Venice Pavilion, were 
part of the festivities. Authorities said the event was peaceful. MEL MELCON / 
Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
