<HEADLINE>
<P>
HELMET BILL VETO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I applaud Gov. Deukmejian's veto of the mandatory motorcycle helmet bill. The 
proposed helmet law embraces the philosophy that it is better to force the 
judgment of the majority on the individual than to grant that person the 
freedom, dignity, and occasional mistakes that all come as a package deal with 
being truly human. 
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, as long as the state reserves the right, at its own discretion, to 
draft a man and send him off to end up face down in a rice paddy somewhere with 
his brains blown out, it has no business telling him he must wear a helmet when 
he rides because otherwise he might get hurt. 
</P>
<P>
JOEL VOELZKE 
</P>
<P>
Tujunga 
</P>
</TEXT>
