Two Lebanese girls drowned after Syrian rocket fire capsized a boat packed with 
refugees fleeing Lebanon's civil war. The boat was ferrying passengers from the 
besieged Christian port of Juniyah to a Hovercraft bound for Cyprus when a 
Syrian rocket battery opened fire. Crew members from the Hovercraft lowered 
