<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUR KILLED, 24 HURT AS CAR HITS TOUR BUS HEAD-ON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WARREN, Me. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four young people were killed and 24 other people were injured when a car 
slammed head-on into a tour bus carrying senior citizens, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred Saturday when the car crossed the center line and hit the 
bus, state police said. All four people in the car were killed when it was hit 
by another vehicle, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
