<P>
Japan Prods Auto Makers: The Japanese government has asked domestic auto makers 
to boost imports of vehicles and parts and it might give them another nudge if 
imports fail to rise, a trade official said. "Our request is not binding. But 
we hope they will listen to our request and import more," the Ministry of 
International Trade and Industry official said. Japan has been under pressure 
from its trading partners to reduce its huge trade surpluses, in which car 
exports have played a major role. 
