<P>
Freuhauf Changes Name: Freuhauf Corp., based in Romulus, Mich., has changed its 
name to K-H Corp. as part of the automotive parts manufacturer's sale of its 
truck trailer and maritime businesses to Terex Corp. On May 5, Toronto-based 
Varity Corp. agreed to buy Freuhauf for $436 million and 55 million shares of 
Varity stock. The name change won't affect that takeover. 
</P>
</TEXT>
