<TEXT>
<P>
First Lexus Cars Shipped: The first 1,000 Lexus LS 400 luxury sedans, Toyota's 
first V-8 four-door luxury sedan, have been shipped to dealers. The model is 
scheduled for introduction Sept. 1. The LS 400 has 250 horsepower, a top speed 
of 150 m.p.h. and a base price of $35,000. It is being priced for positioning 
between American and European luxury cars. With options, LS 400s are expected 
to cost about $38,000. That was the price announced for Nissan Motor Corp.'s 
V-8-powered Infiniti Q45 sedan, slated to appear in showrooms Nov. 8. Lexus 
also will offer a 156-horsepower, V-6-powered four-door sedan called the ES 250 
with a base price of $21,050. 
</P>
