<P>
U.S. Playing Card Corp. Sold: Jesup Group Inc. announced that it has completed 
the sale of U.S. Playing Card Corp. to Bicycle Acquisition Corp. in a deal 
worth more than $95 million. Under the agreement, Jesup Group will own about 
20% of Bicycle Acquisition, a new company formed by Frontenac Co. and 
management, said Jesup spokeswoman Barbara C. Anderson. U.S. Playing Card is 
the world's largest manufacturer and distributor of branded playing cards with 
sales of about $90 million. 
</P>
